# Advanced Features of Simple Table

In this article, we'll explore some of the more advanced features that make Simple Table a powerful tool for data management.

## Custom Column Renderers

One of the most powerful features of Simple Table is the ability to create custom column renderers:

```javascript
const table = new SimpleTable({
  data: users,
  columns: [
    { key: 'name', title: 'Name' },
    { 
      key: 'status', 
      title: 'Status',
      render: (value) => {
        return `<span class="status-badge ${value}">${value}</span>`;
      }
    }
  ]
});
```

## Row Selection

Enable row selection to allow users to interact with your data:

```javascript
const table = new SimpleTable({
  data: products,
  columns: ['id', 'name', 'price'],
  selectable: true,
  onSelect: (selectedRows) => {
    console.log('Selected rows:', selectedRows);
  }
});
```

## Data Export

Export your table data in various formats:

```javascript
// Export to CSV
await table.exportToCSV('data.csv');

// Export to Excel
await table.exportToExcel('data.xlsx');
```

## Real-time Updates

Keep your table in sync with real-time data:

```javascript
// Subscribe to data updates
const unsubscribe = table.subscribeToUpdates((newData) => {
  console.log('Data updated:', newData);
});

// Later, when you're done
unsubscribe();
```

## Performance Optimization

For large datasets, consider these performance tips:

- Use virtual scrolling
- Implement data pagination
- Optimize your render functions
- Use memoization for complex calculations

## Conclusion

These advanced features make Simple Table a versatile tool for any data visualization needs. Experiment with these features to create the perfect table for your application!
